blockcomment:
Bits 62 - 63 (most significant 2) are reserved for the message type masks (error, warning, info)
Bits 25 - 26 are reserved for the operation type masks (create, modify, delete)
Bits 18 - 21 are reserved for the object type masks (node, resource, resource definition, ...)
Bits 0  - 14 are reserved for codes
Type masks (Node, ResDfn, Res, VolDfn, Vol, NetInterface, ...)

name: API_END_OF_IMMEDIATE_ANSWERS
comment: Indicates that the immediate answers to the API call are complete

name: EVENT_RESOURCE_STATE
comment: State of resource based on DRBD status (or other underlying system)

name: EVENT_RESOURCE_DEPLOYMENT_STATE
comment: State of resource based on execution of commands to deploy it

name: KEY_STOR_POOL_ALLOCATION_UNIT
comment: Unit of smallest allocation. The size in KiB as a decimal number.
